subSubSection.paragraph:
('1" 
watsoni
). Its back is dark brown medially, with light brown ocher on both sides of midline of back; sides are pale; underparts have brown ocher midline extending from pectoral region to base of tail; and legs are dark. Tail is slightly longer than body, dark gray basally and flesh colored distally. There are four inguinal teats. Long anterior palatine foramen reaches level of M'; nasals extend beyond premaxila.
